Negation in Datalog is implemented using "Not" operator. The "Not" operator is used to represent the negative facts in Datalog. When a fact is negated, it means that the fact is not true.

To implement negation in your DatalogEngine class, you would need to extend your query, unify and evaluateRule methods to handle the "Not" operator.

Here's a simple way to do it:

Add a method to process negation:

```javascript
processNegation(predicate, args, substitution = {}) {
  const substitutedArgs = this.applySubstitution(substitution, args);
  const facts = this.facts[predicate] || [];

  for (let factArgs of facts) {
    const substitutionResult = this.unify(substitutedArgs, factArgs, {...substitution});
    if (substitutionResult) {
      // If we find a match, that means the negation failed, so we return null
      return null;
    }
  }

  // If we didn't find any matching facts, that means the negation is true
  return substitution;
}
```
Modify your evaluateRule to handle negation:

